picked: Evangeline Lily was Tauriel, a character created specifically for The Hobbit film series and not present in J. R. R. Tolkien's original book. She is an Elven warrior from Mirkwood who falls in love with a human dwarf named Kili. Critics have compared her to the famous elf Legolas (played by Orlando Bloom), because both characters are skilled archers. Some viewers complained that adding the romance between Tauriel and Kili to the story "ruined" it, but others enjoyed watching two people fall in love despite their differences. Because Evangeline Lilly also starred in the TV show Lost and appeared in another Peter Jackson movie called King Kong, she has become a popular actress known for playing strong female leads in action-adventure stories set in magical worlds. Whether you like or dislike Tauriel and her relationship with Kili may depend on how much you enjoy seeing nonhuman races interact with humans and other creatures in Middle Earth. data.sampled: Season 5, episode 309 "Elevator Love Letter" was the last time we see Derek Shepherd (played by Patrick Dempsey) alive and he dies off screen after his car gets hit by a truck on April 16, 2015. His body is later found at the bottom of a ravine, so his death technically happened outside of Grey Sloan Memorial Hospital but due to all previous events taking place inside said hospital I would say it still counts!
